flowRoot.flowPara: Front: Topsoil information and words // logo

text.tspan: * ◊Topsoil can run on any Windows, Mac OS, or Linux system with the latest Java version installed.
* Topsoil is developed and maintained by a team of undergraduates at the College of Charleston.
Topsoil is free and open source, and the code is available to everyone on GitHub.com.
Anyone can download Topsoil and its source code for free.
Users can also contribute to Topsoil's development by submitting found bugs, improvement
ideas, or even code on Topsoil's GitHub repository. Detailed instructions on how to do this are available on Topsoil's page on the CIRDLES website.
Topsoil is a desktop application and Java library for providing interactive visualizations
of geochronological data, developed and maintained by the Cyber Infrastructure Research and Development Lab for the Earth Sciences (CIRDLES).
